# VCF 9.x Lab Environment Quick Reference

This is a **Holodeck nested virtualization lab** running VCF 9.0.x or 9.1.x. All passwords default to `/home/holuser/creds.txt`.

## Key Hostnames & Auth

| Component | Hostname | User | Auth |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| SDDC Manager | `sddcmanager-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `vcf` | Basic Auth |
| VCF Operations | `ops-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `admin` | OpsToken |
| vCenter (Mgmt) | `vc-mgmt-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `administrator@vsphere.local` | Session |
| vCenter (WLD) | `vc-wld01-a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `administrator@wld.sso` | Session |
| NSX (Mgmt) | `nsx-mgmt-01a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `admin` | Basic Auth |
| NSX (WLD) | `nsx-wld01-01a.site-a.vcf.lab` | `admin` | Basic Auth |
| VCF Automation | `auto-a.site-a.vcf.lab` (10.1.1.70/71) | `vmware-system-user` | SSH+sudo |
| VSP Cluster CP | `10.1.1.142` (VIP) | `vmware-system-user` | SSH+sudo |

## Critical Reminders

- **SDDC Manager rotates passwords** ‚Äî check `/v1/credentials` if standard password fails.
- **vCenter SSH host keys change on upgrade** ‚Äî always use `StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new`.
- **vapi-endpoint and trustmanagement often STOPPED** after boot ‚Äî start via `vmon-cli --start`.
- **NSX user IDs are numeric** (`0`=root, `10000`=admin). NSX CLI password-expiration broken on 9.1 ‚Äî use REST API.
- **Component CRDs are cluster-scoped** (`components.api.vmsp.vmware.com`) ‚Äî never use `-A` or `-n` flags.
- **SSH escaping with kubectl** ‚Äî use `-o json` parsed locally, never `custom-columns` through SSH layers.
- **VCF Automation microservice deployments** may remain at 0 replicas after shutdown ‚Äî must be scaled up manually.
- **CSI service account passwords** (`svc-vcfsp-vc-*@vsphere.local`) can be rotated during VCF upgrades ‚Äî reset via `dir-cli password reset` on vCenter.
- **VCF 9.0 vs 9.1**: OpsToken authSource is `local` (9.0) vs `localItem` (9.1). Password management API only exists in 9.1+. VCF Automation sudo is NOPASSWD (9.0) vs password-required (9.1).
- **SDDC Manager credential REMEDIATE** requires: (1) service accounts fixed in vCenter SSO first, (2) stale locks cleared from `platform.lock` table, (3) resource statuses set to ACTIVE in platform DB. Process one resource at a time (10-task concurrency limit).
- **SDDC Manager PostgreSQL** is on `127.0.0.1:5432` (TCP, not socket). Password in `/root/.pgpass`. SSH as `vcf` user can run `psql` without root.
- **SDDC Manager `/v1/resource-locks` API is read-only** ‚Äî cannot DELETE locks via API. Must use direct `psql` access to `DELETE FROM lock`.
- **vCenter `/api/session` returns HTTP 201**, not 200. Accept both when checking session creation success.
- **SCP VMs are EAM-managed on VCF 9.0.x** ‚Äî `PowerOnVM_Task()` via vCenter returns `NoPermission`. Connect directly to ESXi hosts as `root` to power on SCP VMs.
- **VCF Automation VIP (10.1.1.70) can drop after cold boot** ‚Äî kube-vip releases the VIP when istio-ingressgateway has no endpoints (ImagePullBackOff during Antrea CNI init). Fix: `ip addr add 10.1.1.70/32 dev eth0`, restart containerd/kubelet, delete ImagePullBackOff pods. `VCFfinal.py` Task 4b automates this.
- **Supervisor kube-dns endpoint may point to LB IP** after ungraceful shutdown ‚Äî causes vSphere Pod DNS to fail via asymmetric NSX DLB routing. Fix: patch endpoint to CoreDNS pod IPs (`172.16.200.x`). `VCFfinal.py` Task 2c2 automates this.
- **NSX Edge SR STANDBY having `Op_state: down` interfaces is normal** ‚Äî in `ACTIVE_STANDBY` mode, only the ACTIVE SR brings up its interfaces. Check HA status via NSX Policy API `/policy/api/v1/infra/tier-1s/{id}/locale-services/{id}/ha-config` before diagnosing as broken.
- **NSX Edge VMs are registered on WLD ESXi hosts** (not management vCenter) ‚Äî must connect directly to ESXi hosts as `root` to power on/off edge VMs. They're on `esx-06a` (edge-wld01-02a) and `esx-07a` (edge-wld01-01a).
- **VSP service CIDR is `198.18.128.0/17`** ‚Äî not the standard `10.96.0.0/12`. Must include `198.18.0.0/16` in NO_PROXY for containerd/kubelet on VSP nodes, otherwise image pulls from the internal registry (`198.18.128.16:5000`) get routed through Squid proxy and fail with 403.
- **Fleet LCM direct API uses different type names** than suite-api proxy: `NI`‚Üí`OPS_NETWORKS`, `LI`‚Üí`OPS_LOGS`, `FLEET_LCM`‚Üí`VCF_FLEET_LCM`, `SDDC_LCM`‚Üí`VCF_SDDC_LCM`.
- **Fleet LCM shutdown returns HTTP 202** with a `taskId` ‚Äî poll via `GET /fleet-lcm/v1/tasks/{taskId}`.
- **OpsToken authSource varies** in VCF 9.1 builds ‚Äî try both `local` and `localItem`. VCF 9.1 C4 uses `local`.
- **Vault root token is creds.txt password** ‚Äî not `"holodeck"`. Verify with `curl -sk -H "X-Vault-Token: $(cat /home/holuser/creds.txt)" http://10.1.1.1:32000/v1/auth/token/lookup-self`.
- **Vault PKI role `holodeck` default max_ttl is 720h (30 days)** ‚Äî update to 17520h for 2-year certs via `POST /v1/pki/roles/holodeck`.
- **SDDC Manager Bearer token auth** uses `admin@local` username for `/v1/tokens`. Not `vcf` or `administrator@vsphere.local`.
- **opslogs-a SSH user is `vmware-system-user`** ‚Äî root and admin are rejected. opsnet-a has no SSH access at all.
- **auto-platform-a.site-a.vcf.lab (10.1.1.69)** is a separate VM from auto-a (10.1.1.70). SSH: `vmware-system-user`.
- **SDDC Manager Microsoft CA proxy** at `https://ca.vcf.lab/certsrv` ‚Äî impersonates Microsoft ADCS, forwards to Vault PKI on holorouter. Template names in `certrqxt.asp` must use `<Option Value="OID;TemplateName">` format for SDDC Manager's Java regex parser.
- **Technitium DNS requires `vcf.lab` zone** for `ca.vcf.lab` records ‚Äî only `site-a.vcf.lab` and `site-b.vcf.lab` exist by default.
- **pyOpenSSL PKCS7 class removed** in v25+ ‚Äî use `cryptography.hazmat.primitives.serialization.pkcs7.serialize_certificates()` instead.
- **VCF Operations CA validation does NOT follow 301 redirects** ‚Äî certsrv proxy must serve content directly (HTTP 200) for `/certsrv` without trailing slash. VCF Ops Java client treats 301 as failure.
- **SDDC Manager `PUT /v1/certificate-authorities`** requires both `password` and `secret` fields in `microsoftCertificateAuthoritySpec`. Omitting `secret` returns HTTP 400.
- **VCF Ops cert mgmt repo endpoint requires `page`/`pageSize` params** ‚Äî without them, returns HTTP 500. Response key is `vcfRepositoryCertificates` with `certId` field.
- **VCF Ops cert mgmt CSR PEM uses spaces not newlines** ‚Äî must normalize before Vault signing. Field name is `csr` under `certificateSignatureInfo`.
- **VCF Ops cert replace orchestrator**: VROPS (vidb, opslogs, opsnet, fleet/instance/vsp runtimes) completes in minutes. VRSLCM (auto-a, auto-platform-a, ops-a) depends on fleet-upgrade-service health.
- **Fleet-upgrade-service internal error blocks VRSLCM cert replace** ‚Äî tasks stay `NOT_STARTED`. CSR/sign/import still succeed; complete via VCF Operations UI.
- **VCF Ops cert mgmt task status API returns HTTP 500** ‚Äî poll `certificates/query` for issuer change instead.
- **PKCS#7 `serialize_certificates()` reorders certs** ‚Äî DER SET OF sorting puts CA before leaf. Must use custom `build_ordered_pkcs7()` for SDDC Manager compatibility (`certs[0]` = leaf, `certs[1]` = CA).
- **Vault `sign-verbatim` preserves full CSR subject DN** ‚Äî `sign/{role}` strips O/OU/C/L/ST fields. Always use `sign-verbatim/{role}` for SDDC Manager CSRs.
- **Vault CA trust distribution** automated by `confighol-9.1.py` Step 0b ‚Äî imports Vault root CA into vCenter VECS (`dir-cli trustedcert publish`), ESXi castore.pem, NSX trust-management API, SDDC Manager trusted-certificates API, and Linux appliance OS trust stores.
- **SDDC Manager PostgreSQL** ‚Äî Password in `/root/.pgpass` (SSH as `vcf`, use Python `pty.openpty()` to `su` to root). TCP on `127.0.0.1:5432`, database `operationsmanager`.

